Detectives on Sunday arrested two men in Isiolo for allegedly being in possession of fake Euros and "gold". "Abdi Mohamed, 24, and Abdullah Hassan Golle, 23, were arrested on Sunday evening in Isiolo by DCI detectives for being in possession of several bundles of fake currencies and seven metal bars of 'gold'," the DCI tweeted on Monday. The two suspects will be arraigned and charged once investigations are complete. Read: Two South Koreans plead guilty to possessing Sh700m in fake currency Click here for the latest political news        